description: Kat Edmonson is a Brooklyn-based singer-songwriter who specializes in jazz and vintage pop. Her new album ‘Dreamers Do’ features re-imagined Disney songs from the mid-20th century. Bobby Watson is a saxophonist, composer, arranger and educato from Kansas City, Kan. A former member of Art Blakey’s Jazz Messengers, the saxophonist’s new album ‘Keepin’ It Real’ represents a new chapter in his musical life.
